ZCZC GE04
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 142300 UTC
TUESDAY EVENING THE LARGE HIGH OVER THE AZORES WILL BEGIN TO EXTEND A
RIDGE N AND E TOWARD THE FAEROE ISLANDS. THREE SEPARATE LOW PRESSURE SYSTEMS
WILL FORM TO THE N AND E OF THIS RIDGE ONE IN THE ARCTIC OCEAN 994 ONE
IN SW NORWAY 1006 AND ANOTHER WITHIN BISCAY CLOSE TO THE BRITTANY COAST
1006. ON WEDNESDAY ALL SYSTEMS WILL MOV EWARD AND THE S TWO LOW PRESSURES
WILL LOSE THEIR IDENTITY. ON THURSDAY A DEEP ATLANTIC LOW PRESSURE WILL
ARRIVE IN WERN WATERS 981 DISPLACING THE AZORES RIDGE OVER THE BRITISH
ISLES. LITTLE CHANGE THROUGH FRIDAY THOUGH THE RIDGE MAY BECOME FURTHER
DISPLACED EWARD AS THE LOW PRESSURE TRACKS TOWARD THE FAEROE ISLANDS AND
THE AZORES HIGH BEGINS ANOTHER N MIGRATION. TUESDAY EVENING AND WEDNESDAY
STRG WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS MOST NERN N SEA AREAS WITH NEAR GALES CLOSE TO
COASTS OF SCOTLAND AND SCANDINAVIA. NO FURTHER HAZARDOUS WINDS EXP
NNNN